Mediocre food and comically bad service. I went into this place about 3 years ago and left after 40 minutes of not getting served. The manager gave me his card and asked me to return, but there are just too many good options around to return someplace that I left so very hungry. Today I was on my way someplace else when the rain started, so we ducked in, open to giving them another chance. My date went in first, and I thought she was exaggerating when she told me that the host/server had yelled at her, but the rest of the experience suggested that it was plausible. It was labor day Monday,  according to Google Maps I was there from 2:41 to 4:06, not exactly "prime" meal time, the place was less than half full and the empty tables were mostly littered with debris from previous guests. Seems they didn't have enough floor staff, as the one, overworked woman was hostess and busser. Once seated we ordered an entree salad and a burger. 20 minutes later a fried calamari appetizer appeared at our place, and the table next to us (seated after us) got a salad and another calamari.  I told the server "we didn't order that, but we've been waiting 20 minutes and I'll eat whatever" She took it away. The table next to us leaned over and apologized, saying that they'd been, on past visits, the one that doesn't get food. This must be enough of a trend that people expect it, and somehow still return? About 30+ minutes after we ordered my salad arrived, and server told us "burger is on the way", it was, but that was another 4 to 5 minutes before it happened. Meanwhile as she was clearing plates and stuff my date (who was facing away from the bus station) thought she was having a tantrum because of how LOUD she was tossing dishes into the bus tub, and the crashing noise it made. I just thought that the station was set up poorly and she didn't want to take the extra step to get close and gently put dishes in.  The food wasn't bad, my salad was under-dressed/not very tasty, and the well-done burger was dry ( I know, that's what well done is).  At some point the server took our water bottle away from the table, I assumed this was to refill it and return to the table, but that part never happened. After we finished eating, while waiting for the check, I watched the server, in her torn top, with big hole in the back, interact with her phone a few times (looked like one was a pretty long outgoing text) and attempt two 3-point shots of paper debris into the garbage. She was successful at one of them, the other was just left on the floor.  Once we squared away our bill I stopped in the restroom on the way out. It wasn't "fine" see attached photo. Again, my only reason for going into this place was the rain stopped us from going further, and we were very, very close. I had pretty low expectations, which we met in spades. It took us an hour and twenty minutes in a half empty restaurant to get a burger and salad, and the poor service was apologized to us by the next table. I just can't figure out what they are doing right, to stay open YEARS after other competitors have closed up and down Bedford ave in the neighborhood.

I placed my order on Seamless for a delivery. When the delivery person showed up he was angry and said I could never order from the restaurant again. I have a business in the Brooklyn Navy Yard. He called when he was outside the complex and I gave him my exact location and building I was in. The next time I heard from him was about 8 minutes later. He called when he was on my floor but he was so angry and yelling I couldn’t understand what he was saying. I tried to find out where he was to assist him with my location. Once he saw me in the hall, he basically threw the bag at me and stormed off. I immediately called the restaurant to let them know how he was treating customers and although they heard me out and apologized, they mentioned not knowing his side of the story. What personally could I have done to warrant this outburst? I simply ordered food online. They also mentioned the location being far from their address but why would I be able to order from a restaurant on Seamless if it was outside the coordinates for delivery? They did not offer a discount or any other compensation for my treatment. Luckily there are other places to order from without running the risk of this kind of treatment. This one aspect of service and being treated rudely ruined the entire experience with this restaurant.

It takes a lot for me to give a negative review. I work in the industry and I’m very understanding with most things. I believe this place has the potential to be really great! They have awesome drinks specials, and they do brunch every day. The space is rustic and well decorated, and there is a back patio that has a few tables and it brings a lot of wonderful natural light. We ordered wings which never came out and the waitress, who I want to mention was very nice, admittedly forgot, which was a little disappointing since we were the only customers not sitting at the bar. I ordered the steak and eggs and my girlfriend ordered a burger. We both ordered medium rare. It took much longer than it should’ve and we found out why. Mine came out medium-well to well done, and the burger was the most well-done it could be without burning it completely. I don’t write bad reviews for any other reason but to maybe shed light. I’d love this to be a place I could call a regular spot. While environment and service are definitely important, none of it matters if the food isn’t up to par.

THE FRENCH TOAST IS IT! Our bookclub held a monthly meeting here, on the recommendation of a member. Lou was our server that Sat. afternoon , and he skillfully handled our group of 10. There's a well-stocked bar in front, immaculate bathrooms in the middle, and all variations of seating in the back. Did I mention the fluffy, French toast that you could eat without toppings, it was so good?! The menu is varied, the $15 p/p unlimited brunch drinks were well flavored and strong enough. The ambience encourages conversation due to subdued lighting, upbeat, not-too-loud music, and the seating plan. Oh, and the French toast! (Friends said the wings and burgers were fine, but I lost my mind on the French toast, and didn't venture.) Check them out, and ask for Lou.

So, I ordered 2 orders of their lobster mac and cheese for $50 total. Yes, very pricey but they were local so I gave them a try. Immediately as I got to my car, I noticed the strong fishy smell. Still, I gave it a taste and noticed that the 'lobster' meat wasn't lobster at all but im fact, crab. I called the location and explained what was wrong and was basically told that I was wrong and that it was lobster. When I offered to bring back the meal, the man on the phone told me, "I don't see a point in that. We sell hundreds of that item a day. There's nothing we can really do. The lobster is chopped up so that's why you think its crab meat." Um, okay, rude, unprofessional and the reason for my review. Never again!!! I have had their lobster mac before and it was good enough then to return for a second time. Instead of allowing me to return the mac and checking to see, I was indirectly called a liar or a fool. They have lost a customer and I will deter others from here. Not only because of the horrible mac, but the way they handle customer complaints.

I know it was going for a pub feel, but the place looked dark and dingy. It could different use a few more lights. My friend told me about this place and if he didn't I wouldn't of stopped here. I drived by and as I was looking through the door, it did look like any place I wanted to get food lol!!! When I went in at first you feel like you in the wrong place because no said anything until I remembered my friend she's to walk to the back and then I finally came across a server, who to me and my friends to our seats. Now I do have to give them props, because one of my friends had a walker and they were very friendly and kind to accommodate her without a problem. I had the lobster macaroni and cheese and the calamari and my friends had the watermelon salad. I was definitely surprised to find out that this place had food like that. The calamari was definitely one of the best I've ever had was really flavorful and wasn't chewy but it did get chewy once it got cold which wasn't help because they had a lot of fans on which made it feel like you're in a hurricane, and I usually eat my food pretty fast but at the rate the wind was blowing compared to me eating there was no way I could eat it while still good and hot! The lobster macaroni and cheese was really good the only thing I wish they add more Lobster. I have had it other places with more Lobster and the price was cheaper. We also have the bread pudding and black and white cake. The cake was probably the best thing it was so rich and creamy I wanted, but the bread pudding was not sweet at all and was hard. The worst part was the waitress she was nice and everything, but she was so slow, it took us over 10 mins to get soda and ketchup, it took so long we almost forgot about it. Overall I enjoyed the food, but everything else wasn't so good and am not usually negative, on my review am not one of those people lol!!!
